1 also hold an election on the second Tuesday of December in odd-
2 numbered years; and
3 2. The second Tuesday of January and February, the first
4 Tuesday in March and April, the third Tuesday in June, the fourth
5 Tuesday in August, and the first Tuesday after the first Monday in
6 November of any even-numbered year.
7 D. In the event that a regular or special election date occurs
8 on an official state holiday, the election shall be scheduled for
9 the next following Tuesday. In the event that any day of a
10 candidate filing period occurs on a Saturday, Sunday or any official
11 state holiday, that day of the filing period shall be scheduled for
12 the next business day.
13 D. For a special election called by the Governor pursuant to
14 law, the Governor shall be limited to the dates stated in subsection
15 B of this section. Provided, if a vacancy has occurred in the
16 office of United States Representative, State Senator, or State
17 Representative, or in the event of a declared national or state
18 emergency that requires a special election, the Governor may also
19 use the following dates for a special election called pursuant to
20 law:
21 1. The second Tuesday of January of any year;
22 2. The first Tuesday of March of any year;
23 3. The first Tuesday of May of an odd-numbered year;
24 4. The second Tuesday of July of any year;
